Returns a chunker instance. The chunker is really great solution for INSERTING/UPDATING data into the DB. This method can help with a lot of data in the single thread. The example below describes its funcionallity.

```javascript
var chunker = U.chunker('products', 50);

somestream.on('data', U.streamer('<product>', '</product>', function(value, index) {
    var product = value.parseXML();

    // The chunker creates more files with a maximum count of chunks (in our case: 50 products)
    chunker.write(product);

    // Here we can't wait for DB
}));

somestream.on('end', function() {

    // Flush
    chunker.end();

    chunker.each(function(items, next) {
        // here we can update DB

        // ....
        // ....

        // Read next items
        next();

    }, function() {

        // This method is called when the chunker doesn't contain any other items (optional).

        // Cleans up hdd and memory
        chunker.destroy();
    });

    // chunker.read(index, function(err, array) {
    //     array === products (max 50)
    // });

    // Removes all chunk files
    // chunker.clear();

    // Performs clear and it cleans memory
    // chunker.destroy();

});
```

__IMPORTANT__:
Chunker stores items into the different files. A chunker `name` is a name of the file. When is chunker destroyed then the method automatically removes all files.

api.body:
This class supports sending emails via SMTP protocol. `FrameworkMail` supports TLS.

- [Example: Email send](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/email-send)
- [Example: Controller email](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/controller-mail)

```js
// Mail === Global object
var message = new Mail.Message('subject', 'body');
// or
// var message = Mail.create('subject', 'body');

// Set email sender
message.from('my@email.com', 'Peter Sirka');

message.to('friend@email.com');
message.to('family@message.com');

message.send('smtp.yourserver.com');
```

## How to send multiple messages?

```js
var a = new Mail.Message('subject', 'body');
var b = new Mail.Message('subject', 'body');
var c = new Mail.Message('subject', 'body');

a.to('friend@email.com');
a.from('me@email.com');

b.to('friend@email.com');
b.from('me@email.com');

c.to('friend@email.com');
c.from('me@email.com');

Mail.send('smtp.yourserver.com', [a, b, c]);
```

## How to check whether the SMTP server does work?

```js
Mail.try('smtp.yourserver.com', function(err) {
    if (!err)
        console.log('SMTP SERVER WORKS CORRECTLY');
});
```

