## Good to know

### Hash

When the framework registers a new component then changes version hash because of HTTP cache. Therefore your `components.css` and `component.js` have still another hash e.g. `?version=ak38s`.

### Rename static files

You can rename static files `.css` and `.js` of components via config file:

__Default settings__:

```html
static-url-components    : /components.
```

__You can change it to e.g.__:

```html
static-url-components    : /components/all.
```

__The result will be:__
- `/components/all.js`
- `/components/all.css`

Total.js has a simple authorization mechanism. It's built on one delegate function `framework.onAuthorize()`. The authorization is asynchronous.

- You can create your own authorization mechanism (total.js gives open options).
- The authorization delegate is async.
- You can authorize users according to the cookies / headers.
- You can set user roles.
- The authorization delegate adds `authorize` and `unauthorize` flag according to the state.
- Is executed in each request.
- __Delegate does not handle static files.__
- [Example: authorization](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/authorization)
- [Download module: Auth](https://github.com/totaljs/modules/tree/master/Security/auth)

---

![Authorization](resources/authorization.png)

---

## Simple example

Create e.g. definition:

```javascript
framework.onAuthorize = function(req, res, flags, next) {

    // EXAMPLE:
    var userId = req.cookie('user').parseInt();

    if (userId === 0) {
        // unauthorized user
        next(false);
        return;
    }

    var nosql = NOSQL('users');

    nosql.one().where('id', userId).callback(function(err, user) {

        if (err || !user) {
            // unauthorized user
            next(false);
            return;
        }

        // user is authorized
        next(true, user);

        // or assign the user object to request.user:
        /*
            req.user = user;
            next(true);
        */
    });
}
```

Usage in controllers:

```javascript
exports.install = function() {
    F.route('/user/', view_logged,   ['authorize']);
    F.route('/user/', view_unlogged, ['unauthorize']);
}

function view_logged() {
    this.view('logged');
}

function view_unlogged() {
    this.view('unlogged');
}
```

The framework has a simple validation logic. The result from the validation is [ErrorBuilder](#api~ErrorBuilder) and it contains all information about errors.

## The schema validation

- [Documentation: SchemaBuilder](#api~SchemaBuilder)

### Example

Create e.g. definition:

```javascript
NEWSCHEMA('User').make(function(schema) {
    // schema.define(name, type, [required], [filter]);
    schema.define('name', 'String(30)', true);
    schema.define('email', 'Email', true);
    schema.define('age', Number, true);
    schema.define('phone', 'Phone', true);

    // The framework has own built-in validation mechanism for "Email", "Phone" and "Zip" types.
    // Sets the validation for "name" and "age" fields
    schema.setValidate(function(name, value, path, schema, model) {
        switch (name) {
            case 'name':
                return value.length > 0;
            case 'age':
                return value > 15 && value < 80;
        }        
    });

    schema.setSave(function(error, model, options, callback) {
        var nosql = NOSQL('users');
        nosql.insert(model);
        callback(SUCCESS(true));
    });
});

// User.setDefault(...)
// User.setSave(...)
// User.setGet(...)
// User.setQuery(...)
// User.setRemove(...)
```

Resource `default.resource` for error messages:

```html
name        : Please enter your name.
age         : Your age is not allowed.
email       : Please type a valid email address.
phone       : Please type a valid phone number.
```

Some actions in a controller:

```javascript
exports.install = function() {
    F.route('/api/users/create/', json_user_create, ['post', '*User']);
}

// The framework automatically converts the request data according to the schema and automatically handles errors
function json_user_create() {
    var self = this;
    self.body.$save(self.callback());    
}

```

__I have multiple fields with same name, how can I validate them?__
The framework supports the global validation delegate `F.onValidate`. Its implementation:

```javascript
F.onValidate = function(name, value, path, model, schema) {
    switch (name) {
        case 'firstname':
        case 'lastname':
            return value.length > 0 ? 'Name is too short.' : true;
        case 'terms':
            return value.toString().parseBool();
        case 'age':
            var age = value.toString().parseInt();
            return age > 10 && age < 90;
        case 'email':
            return value.isEmail();
    }
}
```

## Note: ErrorBuilder transformation

As default are errors in `ErrorBuilder` serialized into the JSON like Object Array. You can rewrite this transformations via [ErrorBuilder.addTransform()](#api~ErrorBuilder~ErrorBuilder.addTransform) and [ErrorBuilder.setTransform()](api~ErrorBuilder~ErrorBuilder.setDefaultTransform).

```json
[{ "name":"Property name", "error":"Error message", "path":"Path in the current object", "index":0 }]
```

### How to check errors on client-side?

```javascript
$.ajax('/add/', { type: 'POST', data: JSON.stringify({ age: 100 }), success: function(response) {

    if (typeof(response) === 'string')
        response = JSON.parse(response);

    // Check erros
    if (response instanceof Array) {
        showErrors(response);
        return;
    }

    // SUCCESS
});
```

> Total.js is doing the dirty job for you. Its core has implemented good tools to improve development and rendering website for all web browsers.

## Release mode

- The framework sets reasonable HTTP cache for the static files (IMG, JS, CSS).
- The framework clears used resources in a time loop.
- The release mode returns highly rated content.

