## Prevention for multiple requesting

If the server doesn't reply quickly, then the web browser can send the request again. We recorded the problem in __Chrome__ web browser.

### total.js prevention

```javascript
exports.install = function() {
    // Prevention for multipe requests from one browser
    F.route('/', delay_operation, ['delay']);
};

function delay_operaiton() {
    var self = this;

    console.log('I am here.');

    setTimeout(function() {
        self.view('some-view');
    }, 10000);
}
```

### Important change for nginx

```lua
http {
    # VERY IMPORTANT FOR "DELAY" FLAG
    proxy_http_version 1.1;
}
```

## Too many open files

If the framework throws `Too many open files` exception then we must enable [default-maximum-file-descriptors](#api~FrameworkConfiguration~default-maximum-file-descriptors) or increase the system limit via terminal `$ ulimit -v unlimited`.

```html
// The framework opens max. 10 files together and waits while they are not closed.
default-maximum-file-descriptors        : 10
```

## How to develop projects?

The project must be created through the models with schemas. The schema must contain a whole business logic because the schema can be shared between projects (or can be injected) and for unit-tests too. Total.js models support error handling, validations, workflows, transformations, operations and basic CRUD operations. The framework can parse some requests as schemas. The model can be linked with other schemas.

```javascript
NEWSCHEMA('User').make(function(schema) {

    // Properties
    schema.define('id', Number);
    schema.define('email', 'Email', true);
    schema.define('created', Date);

    // Defaults:
    schema.setDefault(function(name) {
        switch (name) {
            case 'created':
                return new Date();
        }
    });

    // CRUD
    schema.setGet(function(error, options, callback) {
        error.push('not-implemented');
        callback();
    });

    schema.setSave(function(error, model, options, callback) {
        error.push('not-implemented');
        callback();
    });

    schema.setQuery(function(error, options, callback) {
        error.push('not-implemented');
        callback();
    });

    schema.setRemove(function(error, options, callback) {
        error.push('not-implemented');
        callback();
    });
});
```

__How to use schemas with routing?__

```javascript
exports.install = function() {
    F.route('/api/users/create/', json_user_create, ['post', '*User']);
    F.route('/api/users/', json_user_query);
};

function json_user_create() {
    var self = this;
    var options = {};
    // controller.body contains a validated schema
    self.body.$save(options, self.callback());
}

function json_user_query() {
    var self = this;
    var options = {};
    GETSCHEMA('User').query(options, self.callback());
}
```

