function filehander_action(req, res) {
    // easy hack
    res.noCompress = true;
    res.file('myjavascript.js');
}
```

__Isomorphic code__ (`+v1.9.0`) is one code for server-side and client-side together. Total.js evals isomorphic code on server-side and store it in `isomorphic` variable (a global variable). The framework sends isomorphic code to client-side when is needed. Isomorphic code is stored on server-side in `/isomorphic` directory. The framework loads all isomorphic codes after start.

## Example

Filename on server-side: `/isomorphic/shared.js`:

```javascript
// Very important for transferring of code between server-side and client-side.
// The framework supports several ways how to transfer code into the client-side.
exports.url = '/shared.js';

// Change manually isomorphic library name:
// exports.id = 'my-new-name';

exports.getName = function() {
    // is_server == is a global variable
    // is_client == is a global variable
    return 'total.js' + (is_server ? ' (called from server)' : ' (called from client)');
};
```

__Server__:

```javascript
console.log(isomorphic.shared.getName());
// Output: total.js (called from server)
```

__Client__:

```html
<script src="/shared.js"></script>
<script>
    console.log(isomorphic.shared.getName());
    // Output: total.js (called from client)
</script>
```

### FAQ

- `framework` on client-side is `null`
- variables `is_server` and `is_client` are available on server-side and client-side together

